tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE lighting_design (
    fixture_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    fixture_type VARCHAR(255),
    fixture_brand VARCHAR(255),
    fixture_specifications TEXT,
    installation_instructions TEXT,
    client_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE client_consultation (
   consultation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   client_name VARCHAR(50),
   consultation_date DATE,
   fixture_id INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (fixture_id) REFERENCES lighting_fixture(fixture_id)
);

CREATE TABLE lighting_fixtures (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  brand VARCHAR(50),
  model VARCHAR(50),
  wattage INT,
  color_temperature VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE client_consultations (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  consultation_date DATE,
  client_name VARCHAR(50),
  designer VARCHAR(50),
  notes TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE projects (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  project_name VARCHAR(50),
  client_id INT,
  designer_id INT,
  budget DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE lighting_fixtures (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    type VARCHAR(50),
    wattage INT,
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
)

CREATE TABLE installation_instructions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    fixture_id INT,
    instructions TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE client_consultations (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT,
    consultant_id INT,
    meeting_date DATE,
    notes TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE clients (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    company VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    phone VARCHAR(20)
)

CREATE TABLE consultants (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    expertise VARCHAR(100)
)
